classes.name: CacheController
classes.docstring: An interface to see if request should cached or not.

methods.name: cached_request
methods.docstring:
Return a cached response if it exists in the cache, otherwise
return False.

methods.name: cache_response
methods.docstring:
Algorithm for caching requests.

This assumes a requests Response object.

methods.name: update_cached_response
methods.docstring:
On a 304 we will get a new set of headers that we want to
update our cached value with, assuming we have one.

This should only ever be called when we've sent an ETag and
gotten a 304 as the response.

functions.name: parse_uri
functions.docstring:
Parses a URI using the regex given in Appendix B of RFC 3986.

(scheme, authority, path, query, fragment) = parse_uri(uri)
